ProtoResult:
. "If $\sum a_n$ converges, then for each $\epsilon>0$ there 
   is an integer $K$ such that $$ \left|\sum_{n=k}^\infty 
   a_n\right|<\epsilon \quad if\quad k\ge K; $$ that is, $$ 
   \lim_{k\to\infty}\sum_{n=k}^\infty a_n=0. $$"
